-----ABOUT FLUXER-----

Fluxer is a free, open-source chat platform built as an alternative to Discord — text channels, voice and video calls, servers (called "communities"), roles, and moderation tools, all the stuff you're already used to.

-----WHAT MAKES IT DIFFERENT-----


Open source. The entire platform's code is public on GitHub under the AGPL v3 license. Anyone can inspect it, audit it, or contribute to it — nothing is hidden.
Self-hostable. Communities can run their own independent Fluxer server instead of relying on one company's servers. That's exactly what we're doing — New Game+ runs on our own dedicated hardware, not Discord's, not even Fluxer's own official servers.
No forced verification. Since we run our own instance, nobody outside our community decides what data gets collected or who it gets shared with.
Built-in voice & video. Powered by LiveKit, an open-source real-time media engine — same category of tech that powers a lot of modern video platforms.


-----HOW IT'S BUILT-----

Fluxer isn't one giant program — it's split into a bunch of smaller specialized services (API, gateway, media handling, voice, search, and more) that all work together behind the scenes. For us as users, none of that complexity matters; it just means the people building Fluxer designed it to actually scale.

-----WHERE IT'S HEADED-----

Fluxer is actively developed and growing — the official public instance already has well over 100,000 users. Self-hosting support is brand new (just added this month), which means we're genuinely early to this — most of the internet hasn't even found out self-hosting Fluxer is possible yet.

-----THE BOTTOM LINE-----

It looks and feels like Discord, works like Discord, but it's ours — our server, our rules, our data.
